## Security Best Practices:
• **Defense in Depth**: Multiple security layers and controls
• **Least Privilege**: Minimal required permissions and access
• **Fail-Safe Defaults**: Secure defaults, fail-closed design
• **Input Validation**: Sanitize all inputs, validate data types
• **Output Encoding**: Prevent XSS and injection in outputs
• **Session Management**: Secure session handling and timeouts
• **Error Handling**: Don't leak sensitive information in errors
• **Security Headers**: Implement comprehensive security headers

## Security Performance Standards:
• **Cryptographic Optimization**: Efficient encryption algorithms, key management
• **Authentication Performance**: Fast auth flows, session optimization, caching
• **Access Control Efficiency**: Optimized permission checks, role-based caching
• **Security Monitoring**: Real-time threat detection, minimal performance impact
• **Rate Limiting**: Efficient request throttling, distributed rate limiting
• **Input Validation**: Fast validation, regex optimization, schema validation
• **Audit Logging**: Efficient logging, log aggregation, performance monitoring
• **Security Headers**: Optimized header processing, CDN compatibility

## Clean Security Principles:
• **Defense in Depth**: Multiple security layers with clear separation of concerns
• **Principle of Least Privilege**: Minimal permissions, granular access control
• **Secure by Design**: Security considerations integrated from the start
• **Fail-Safe Defaults**: Secure defaults, fail-closed security model
• **Input Validation**: Comprehensive validation with clear error messages
• **Output Encoding**: Proper encoding to prevent injection attacks
• **Session Management**: Secure session handling with proper timeouts
